<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<strong><a href="./RavenRed">RavenRed</a></strong>: Just a quick query as to the way in which stealth works. Zizzo's killerbunnies provides the calculation, but I was wondering whether the range from the character to the monster makes for a graduated calculation, or if the standard stealth calculation is applied whenever a char enters a monster's perception range REGARDLESS of the distance from the monster. Thanks in advance.  </div><div id="footer">


